org.twdata.kokua.script.flow
Class Continuation

java.lang.Object
  org.twdata.kokua.script.flow.Continuation
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable
public class Continuation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable

Representation of continuations in a Web environment.

Because a user may click on the back button of the browser and restart a saved computation in a continuation, each Continuation becomes the parent of a subtree of continuations.

If there is no parent Continuation, the created continuation becomes the root of a tree of Continuations.

getContinuation

public Continuation getContinuation(int level)
Return the ancestor continuation situated levels above the current continuation. The current instance is considered to be at level 0. The parent continuation of the receiving instance at level 1, its parent is at level 2 relative to the receiving instance. If level is bigger than the depth of the tree, the root of the tree is returned.

Parameters:
level - an int value
Returns:
a Continuation value
